                    <span>The crew of Apollo 7 earned the respect of the entire nation for taking the first flight after the tragic Apollo 1 fire. As I learn more about Mr. Cunningham, I am even more impressed. The All American Boys is part autobiography and part analysis of NASA past and present. It is not a detailed flight by flight chronology. Instead, it provides an authoritative perspective that cuts through the clutter and sanitized version we often get. To his credit, Mr. Cunningham communicates in a thoughtful manner without taking cheap shots at his former colleagues.<P>On a personal note, Mr. Cunningham responded to an autograph request within 7 days (small fee - check his website for details). This helped cement my respect for Mr. Cunningham. You will enjoy this book.<P>Mike Hill</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Priceless information. Needed a co-author.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>4</span>
